## Microsoft Coreutils for Windows (MIT)

- Repository: https://github.com/microsoft/coreutils
- Upstream: https://github.com/uutils/coreutils, https://github.com/uutils/findutils,
  https://github.com/uutils/grep
- Copyright: uutils developers, Microsoft Corporation
- License: MIT

Windows desktop builds may download and bundle `coreutils.exe` (multi-call binary)
via `scripts/fetch_windows_coreutils.sh`, then install applet hardlinks under
`~/.dq-teams/bin/coreutils/` for `exec_shell` PATH injection. This replaces the
need for Git Bash to run POSIX utilities on Windows host / win-token backends.
